(2, 'elephant', 'elephant', '象 (n.)', 'n.', '/''elɪf(ə)nt/', '{"meaning":"象 (n.)","examples":["A trunk distinguishes the elephant. — 长鼻是象的特征。","So the part of the elephant I experience applies what we know about people and how we apply that to UX design. — 所以，我体验的那部分的大象就是我们对人的了解和我们将我们的了解应用于用户体验设计。","Tom: No.Although 75% of its raw materials is elephant dung, it is light delicate fragrance instead of stink. This is due to its special fabrication technology. — 不，尽管这种纸里75％的原料都是大象的粪便，但它不但不臭，反而有一种淡淡的清香，这是源于它的特殊的制造工艺。"],"etymology":null}', 2156),
